  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.0\nOn this page\nLevel: beginner\nBy default, a new section page in the mobile application contains a single group of fields: **General information**. This group of fields cannot be renamed or deleted.\nYou can add the rest of columns, column groups and details on the section page manually.\n## Add columns to page\u200b\n1. Open the System Designer by clicking ![btn_system_designer.png](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/mobile_app_setup/BPMonlineHelp/mobile_app_setup_pages/btn_system_designer.png).\n2. Click **Mobile application wizard** in the \"System setup\" block.\n3. Select the workplace to edit and click **Open**.\n4. Click the **Set up sections** button.\n5. Select a section in the list and click **Page setup**.\n6. Click the **New column** button in the column group where you need to add a field (Fig. 1).\nFig. 1 Adding fields to a page\n![Fig.\u00a01 Adding fields to a page](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/mobile_app_setup/BPMonlineHelp/mobile_app_setup_pages/scr_mobile_wizard_new_column_page.png)\n7. Select a column in the **Select column** window and click **Select** (Fig. 2).\nFig. 2 Selecting a column for adding to page\n![Fig.\u00a02 Selecting a column for adding to page](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/mobile_app_setup/BPMonlineHelp/mobile_app_setup_pages/scr_mobile_wizard_new_column.png)\n8. To change the order of the fields on the page, drag and drop them with the left mouse button.\n9. Click the **Save** button (Fig. 3).\nFig. 3 Saving a mobile app section page with the new column\n![Fig.\u00a03 Saving a mobile app section page with the new column](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/mobile_app_setup/BPMonlineHelp/mobile_app_setup_pages/scr_mobile_wizard_with_column.png)\n10. Click **Save** on the mobile application wizard page.\nAs a result, the changes will become available for all users.\n## Add column group to page\u200b\nYou can add field groups to sections, including groups that are not available in the primary application. The **General information** group cannot be renamed or deleted, but you can add more fields to it.\nTo add a field group on the section page:\n1. Open the mobile wizard and open the section page for editing (perform steps **1\u20135** listed in the \"[Add columns to page](https://academy.creatio.com#XREF_78674)\" block).\n2. Select the **Column group** command in the **New** menu (Fig. 4).\nFig. 4 Adding a field group\n![Fig.\u00a04 Adding a field group](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/mobile_app_setup/BPMonlineHelp/mobile_app_setup_pages/scr_mobile_wizard_new_group_column.png)\n3. Enter a title and a name for the field group.\n1. In the **Caption** field, specify the name that will display in the mobile app.\n2. The **Name** field is the internal name of the field group and can only contain Latin letters without special symbols.\n4. Save the settings by clicking **OK**. (Fig. 5).\nFig. 5 Setting up a field group\n![Fig.\u00a05 Setting up a field group](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/mobile_app_setup/BPMonlineHelp/mobile_app_setup_pages/scr_mobile_wizard_group_column_new.png)\n5. A new empty field group will appear on the section page (Fig. 6). Add fields to it and save the changes on the page.\nFig. 6 Adding columns to a column group\n![Fig.\u00a06 Adding columns to a column group](https://academy.creatio.com/guides/sites/en/files/documentation/user/en/mobile_app_setup/BPMonlineHelp/mobile_app_setup_pages/scr_mobile_wizard_column_group_column.png)\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Set up mobile app workplaces](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1391)\n[Set up mobile application section list](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1393)\n[Set up mobile application detail](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1395)",
